## Reading Markdown Files

Use AGENTMAP.md first for file search/discovery.
Flow: read AGENTMAP.md -> identify file -> read AGENT:NAV -> jump to section.

AGENT:NAV appears immediately after frontmatter so you can 
read a files first 50 lines then use AGENT:NAV to target reads.

- If purpose does not match your task stop reading.
- Use s;n ranges: Read(offset=s; limit=n).
- `>` is a hint for subsections that are not listed directly in the nav.

## After Editing or Creating Markdown Files

1. Run: `agentmap update <changed files>` — refreshes line numbers; adds nav blocks to new files
2. Run: `agentmap check <files> --warn-unreviewed` — checks for auto-generated descriptions (marked with `~`)
3. For each file with unreviewed descriptions: edit the nav block to replace `~description` with your own description (remove the `~` prefix)
4. Run: `agentmap update <files>` again — syncs AGENTMAP.md index with your descriptions
5. Commit
